    "sections": [
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Introduction",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.1",
            "summary": "This supervisory statement is addressed to UK Solvency II firms and to the Society of Lloyd's, its members and managing agents. It sets out the Prudential Regulation Authority's (PRA's) expectations o",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.2",
            "summary": "In particular, this statement expands on the following topics:",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.3",
            "summary": "This statement should be read alongside the Solvency Capital Requirement Parts and Minimum Capital Requirement Part of the PRA Rulebook.",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.4",
            "summary": "This statement expands on the PRA’s general approach as set out in its insurance approach document.1 By clearly and consistently explaining its expectations of firms in relation to the particular area",
            "as_at_date": "01/01/2016"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.5",
            "summary": "This statement has been subject to public consultation2 and reflects the feedback that was received by the PRA.",
            "as_at_date": "01/01/2016"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.6",
            "summary": "Firms should also refer to:",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Undertaking specific parameters",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.1",
            "summary": "Firms may apply to the PRA to replace a subset of parameters with undertaking specific parameters when calculating the life, non-life and health underwriting risk modules.",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.2",
            "summary": "Firms should be aware that undertaking specific parameters must be calibrated on the basis of the firm's internal data or on the basis of data which is directly relevant for the operations of the firm",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.3",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Calculation of the Solvency Capital Requirement",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.1",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.2",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.3",
            "summary": "A firm may apply to the PRA to waive or modify Solvency Capital Requirement – Internal Models 8.1, if ther",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.4",
            "summary": "If a firm fails to implement the plan to restore compliance referred to in [Solvency Capital Requirement – Internal Models 9.1](/pra-rules/solvency-capital-requirement---internal-models#553387bc2a034b",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.5",
            "summary": "No particular method for the calculation of the probability distribution forecast is prescribed by PRA rules.",
            "as_at_date": "01/01/2016"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.6",
            "summary": "For the purposes of Solvency Capital Requirement – Internal Models 11.8(1), the PRA would only approve div",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.7",
            "summary": "If a firm cannot derive the SCR directly from the probability distribution forecast generated by its internal model, then the firm may apply to the PRA for a waiver of [Solvency Capital Requirement – ",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
